{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure mode is cross-module handoff: three source clients/feeders must be wired into the summary input builder. A unit test of one function would miss wiring/omission bugs between modules. Real network/OS is not required because source adapters can be in-process fakes, and behavior does not depend on LLM output quality.","test_description":"Run the report assembly pipeline with three stubbed source modules returning distinct sentinel values; assert the payload handed to summary-generation contains all three source sections/fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is module interaction/error-propagation behavior: collector failure must be translated into section-level fallback while the rest of report generation continues. Unit is too low because the failure appears at boundary between source adapter, orchestrator, and renderer. System rejected: behavior text does not require real network outage mechanics, only correct handling once unavailability is surfaced.","test_description":"Execute pipeline with two source stubs returning data and one stub raising an unavailable error; assert report still builds and includes `data unavailable` note for only the failed section.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.11,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on model judgment/output fidelity (whether generated narrative preserves key values). Deterministic stubs cannot detect hallucination, omission, or misstatement, so Integration would hide real failures. Workflow rejected because this behavior targets a single generation quality step, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Feed representative real input datasets into the real summary model and evaluate whether generated narrative preserves required key values/facts (with rubric or automated factual checks plus sampled human review).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary is end-to-end infrastructure: real API calls/data collection path and actual email transport/inbox delivery. In-process mocks can pass while real SMTP/provider/inbox behavior fails. Agentic rejected because behavior criterion is delivery-to-inbox correctness, not LLM output quality/decision quality.","test_description":"Run scheduled script in an environment wired to real internal endpoints (or staging equivalents) and a real mailbox; verify one full run sends a report email that is received by configured recipient with expected structure.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core failure is orchestration/state handoff across modules and runs: email failure handling, local persistence, and retry logic. This can be caught with a failing email adapter fake plus real local filesystem state between two invocations. System considered but rejected because behavior text does not require validating real provider/network outage semantics, only fallback+retry behavior after an unreachable error signal.","test_description":"First invocation: email sender stub raises unreachable error; assert report is persisted locally. Second invocation (simulated next run): sender succeeds; assert persisted report is retried/sent and local pending artifact is cleared or marked delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.09,"Integration":0.67,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
